#. <section class="sutta" id="an11.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an11.12:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Anussativagga"
msgstr "2. Recollection"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an11.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Dutiyamahānāmasutta"
msgstr "12. With Mahānāma (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an11.12:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

# BB omits this, saying that the introduction is the same as the previous sutta. Since the PTS has the same reading, and no variants are noted, this must be an oversight.
msgctxt "an11.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena mahānāmo sakko gilānā vuṭṭhito hoti aciravuṭṭhito "
"gelaññā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Mahānāma the Sakyan had recently recovered from an illness."

msgctxt "an11.12:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:"
msgstr "At that time several mendicants were making a robe for the Buddha …"

msgctxt "an11.12:1.4"
msgid "“niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.333"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an11.12:2.1"
msgid "Assosi kho mahānāmo sakko:"
msgstr "Mahānāma the Sakyan heard about this."

msgctxt "an11.12:2.2"
msgid "“sambahulā kira bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:2.3"
msgid "‘niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo "
"sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "an11.12:2.5"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard this:"

msgctxt "an11.12:2.6"
msgid "‘sambahulā kira bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti—"
msgstr "several mendicants are making a robe for the Buddha, thinking that"

msgctxt "an11.12:2.7"
msgid "niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"when his robe was finished and the three months of the rains residence had "
"passed the Buddha would set out wandering."

msgctxt "an11.12:2.8"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no, bhante, nānāvihārehi viharataṃ kenassa vihārena vihātabban”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Now, we spend our life in various ways. Which of these should we practice?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an11.12:3.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma."
msgstr "“Good, good, Mahānāma!"

msgctxt "an11.12:3.2"
msgid ""
"Etaṃ kho, mahānāma, tumhākaṃ patirūpaṃ kulaputtānaṃ yaṃ tumhe tathāgataṃ "
"upasaṅkamitvā puccheyyātha:"
msgstr ""
"It’s appropriate that respectable people such as you come to me and ask:"

msgctxt "an11.12:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘tesaṃ no, bhante, nānāvihārehi viharataṃ kenassa vihārena vihātabban’ti?"
msgstr "‘We spend our life in various ways. Which of these should we practice?’"

msgctxt "an11.12:3.4"
msgid "Saddho kho, mahānāma, ārādhako hoti, no assaddho;"
msgstr "The faithful succeed, not the faithless."

msgctxt "an11.12:3.5"
msgid "āraddhavīriyo ārādhako hoti, no kusīto;"
msgstr "The energetic succeed, not the lazy."

msgctxt "an11.12:3.6"
msgid "upaṭṭhitassati ārādhako hoti, no muṭṭhassati;"
msgstr "The mindful succeed, not the unmindful."

msgctxt "an11.12:3.7"
msgid "samāhito ārādhako hoti, no asamāhito;"
msgstr "Those with immersion succeed, not those without immersion."

msgctxt "an11.12:3.8"
msgid "paññavā ārādhako hoti, no duppañño."
msgstr "The wise succeed, not the witless."

msgctxt "an11.12:3.9"
msgid ""
"Imesu kho tvaṃ, mahānāma, pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya cha dhamme uttari "
"bhāveyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"When you’re grounded on these five things, go on to develop six further "
"things."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an11.12:4.1"
msgid "Idha tvaṃ, mahānāma, tathāgataṃ anussareyyāsi:"
msgstr "Firstly, you should recollect the Realized One:"

msgctxt "an11.12:4.2"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfect, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an11.12:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, mahānāma, samaye ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the Realized One their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an11.12:4.4"
msgid "ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti tathāgataṃ ārabbha."
msgstr "At that time their mind is unswerving, based on the Realized One."

msgctxt "an11.12:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ujugatacitto kho pana, mahānāma, ariyasāvako labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati "
"dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple whose mind is unswerving finds joy in the meaning and the "
"teaching, and finds joy connected with the teaching."

msgctxt "an11.12:4.6"
msgid ""
"Pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vediyati, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"When you’re joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, "
"the body becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, you feel bliss. And "
"when you’re blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "an11.12:4.7"
msgid ""
"Imaṃ kho tvaṃ, mahānāma, buddhānussatiṃ gacchantopi bhāveyyāsi, ṭhitopi "
"bhāveyyāsi, nisinnopi bhāveyyāsi, sayānopi bhāveyyāsi, kammantaṃ "
"adhiṭṭhahantopi bhāveyyāsi, puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasantopi bhāveyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"You should develop this recollection of the Buddha while walking, standing, "
"sitting, lying down, while engaged in work, and while at home with your "
"children."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.334"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an11.12:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ tvaṃ, mahānāma, dhammaṃ anussareyyāsi … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, you should recollect the teaching …"

msgctxt "an11.12:5.2"
msgid "saṅghaṃ anussareyyāsi … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "an11.12:5.3"
msgid "attano sīlaṃ anussareyyāsi … pe …"
msgstr "your own ethical conduct …"

msgctxt "an11.12:5.4"
msgid "attano cāgaṃ anussareyyāsi … pe …"
msgstr "your own generosity …"

msgctxt "an11.12:5.5"
msgid "devatā anussareyyāsi:"
msgstr "the deities …"

msgctxt "an11.12:5.6"
msgid "‘santi devā cātumahārājikā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.7"
msgid "santi devā tatuttari."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.8"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpāya saddhāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthūpapannā, mayhampi "
"tathārūpā saddhā saṃvijjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.9"
msgid "Yathārūpena sīlena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.10"
msgid "sutena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.11"
msgid "cāgena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.12"
msgid ""
"paññāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthūpapannā, mayhampi tathārūpā "
"paññā saṃvijjatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an11.12:5.13"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, mahānāma, samaye ariyasāvako attano ca tāsañca devatānaṃ saddhañca "
"sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ samaye "
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom of both themselves and the deities their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an11.12:5.14"
msgid "ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti devatā ārabbha."
msgstr "At that time their mind is unswerving, based on the deities."

msgctxt "an11.12:5.15"
msgid ""
"Ujugatacitto kho pana, mahānāma, ariyasāvako labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati "
"dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple whose mind is unswerving finds joy in the meaning and the "
"teaching, and finds joy connected with the teaching."

msgctxt "an11.12:5.16"
msgid ""
"Pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vediyati, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"When you’re joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, "
"the body becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, you feel bliss. And "
"when you’re blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "an11.12:5.17"
msgid ""
"Imaṃ kho tvaṃ, mahānāma, devatānussatiṃ gacchantopi bhāveyyāsi, ṭhitopi "
"bhāveyyāsi, nisinnopi bhāveyyāsi, sayānopi bhāveyyāsi, kammantaṃ "
"adhiṭṭhahantopi bhāveyyāsi, puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasantopi "
"bhāveyyāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"You should develop this recollection of the deities while walking, standing, "
"sitting, lying down, while engaged in work, and while at home with your "
"children.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an11.12:5.18"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
